# Open House Router

Next.js 14 App Router app with TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, and SQLite (better-sqlite3).

## Architecture

- **Frontend**: React client components with SWR for data fetching (5s polling)
- **Backend**: Next.js API routes (App Router `route.ts` handlers)
- **Database**: SQLite via `better-sqlite3` (synchronous, file-based at `data/open-house.db`)
- **Maps**: Leaflet + OpenStreetMap tiles (dynamically imported, no SSR)
- **Routing**: OSRM public demo server (`router.project-osrm.org`) for travel matrices and geometry
- **Geocoding**: Nominatim (`nominatim.openstreetmap.org`)
- **Ads**: Gated video ad system with 10-minute cooldown via `AdGateProvider` context

## Key Constraints

- `better-sqlite3` is a native C++ addon — must be in `serverComponentsExternalPackages` in next.config.mjs
- OSRM public server has rate limits — fallback to haversine estimates for >100 coordinates
- All external APIs are free (no API keys) — OSRM, Nominatim, OpenStreetMap
- SQLite requires persistent disk — deployed to Fly.io with a mounted volume, NOT serverless

## Branching & Deployment

- `main` is protected (requires PR + CI + review), auto-deploys to Fly.io on merge
- `dev` is the working branch — feature branches PR into `dev`, then `dev` PRs into `main`
- CI: lint + typecheck + build (GitHub Actions)
- CD: `fly deploy --remote-only` on push to main

## Project Structure

```
src/
  app/              # Next.js App Router pages and API routes
    api/sessions/   # All REST endpoints under /api/sessions/[id]/...
    session/[id]/   # Main session page (single large client component)
    page.tsx        # Home page (create/join session)
    layout.tsx      # Root layout with AdGateProvider
  components/       # React components
    AdGateProvider  # Ad gate context + modal
    MapView         # Leaflet map (dynamic import, no SSR)
  lib/              # Server-side utilities
    db.ts           # SQLite schema, queries, CRUD
    optimizer.ts    # Route optimization (greedy + 2-opt)
    osrm.ts         # OSRM API client
  types/            # TypeScript interfaces
```
